      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm planning a trip to chicago next month with some friends. we want to find a cool area to stay in but we're kinda worried about safety. can u give us some advice on which neighborhoods are good for tourists and which ones we should probably avoid staying in or walking through at night?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, I'd be happy to help. For a safe and enjoyable stay in Chicago, you may want to consider staying in the West Loop or River North neighborhood. They both offer easy access to tourist attractions and amenities such as museums, dining, and nightlife. The South Loop is another good choice for short-term visitors as it is also safe and vibrant. As for \"avoid,\" I'd recommend not walking through the Near North Side late at night as it has been reported to have higher crime rates, especially around the outskirts of downtown and near the airport. However, most tourist areas remain safe, especially since they're well-lit and bustling with people during daytime hours. Make sure to always be aware of your surroundings and avoid risky behavior for your safety. Enjoy your trip to Chicago!",
